1
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:13,417
- [lock clunking]
- [door creaks open]

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,958
- [keys jangling]
- [high heels clacking]

3
00:00:16,042 --> 00:00:18,125
[soft tense music playing]

4
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:23,250
[Jittri] We don't have much time.

5
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,667
If you want to survive,
listen to me carefully.

6
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,625
Because I'm your only way out.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,375
I already have a lawyer.

8
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,917
[Jittri] Fire him.

9
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,500
He can't help you.

10
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:42,917
Anan will do whatever it takes
to put you in prison.

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,333
And you'll never get out again.

12
00:00:49,917 --> 00:00:52,083
Is this how you always do things?

13
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:53,958
Is this how you get so many clients?

14
00:00:54,042 --> 00:00:56,042
You threaten them, make them afraid.

15
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:59,375
And then act like
you're their only way out.

16
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:01,375
You've handled plenty of cases, right?

17
00:01:02,458 --> 00:01:05,000
So if you dare, tell me I'm wrong.

18
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:13,167
Let me be your lawyer.

19
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:16,250
I'll make sure you never spend
a single day in prison.

20
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:17,792
Why would you help me?

21
00:01:20,917 --> 00:01:23,542
A judge's son kills a police chief's son.

22
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:27,667
A case this big means free publicity.
Who wouldn't want it?

23
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:29,208
[Mek] You should just go.

24
00:01:29,292 --> 00:01:31,750
I don't want to be a tool
for a lawyer like you.

25
00:01:33,292 --> 00:01:34,458
A lawyer like me?

26
00:01:34,542 --> 00:01:37,583
You want me to list
all the shady shit you've done?

27
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:41,292
Depends on who you ask.

28
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:44,375
All my clients seem happy.

29
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:49,500
You still have time to decide.

30
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:52,208
But be quick.

31
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:56,208
I don't know what the conflict was
between you and Anan's son.

32
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:58,417
But remember one thing.

33
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:01,583
Someone's dead.

34
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:04,458
And someone has to pay for it.

35
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,292
[music darkens]

36
00:02:08,208 --> 00:02:11,417
[footsteps departing]

37
00:02:16,125 --> 00:02:17,375
[door opens]

38
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:19,000
[door closes]

39
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:24,625
[music rises]

40
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:27,625
[music concludes]

41
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:34,625
THE EVIL LAWYER

42
00:02:34,708 --> 00:02:37,750
[unsettling music playing]

43
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:04,208
[music intensifies]

44
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:13,000
[music builds]

45
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:14,375
[camera shutters clicking]

46
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:15,708
[music concludes]

47
00:03:15,792 --> 00:03:18,417
[officer] Mek Piriyawich. On your feet.

48
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:21,375
Your lawyer's here. You made bail.

49
00:03:25,667 --> 00:03:26,750
[Mek sighs]

50
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:29,292
Let's go.

51
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,958
[unsettling music playing]

52
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:36,958
- [Mek] Thanks, Uncle.
- Don't mention it.

53
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,583
Oh, your father's here.

54
00:03:56,083 --> 00:03:57,375
[Tom speaks indistinctly]

55
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:58,667
[sighs]

56
00:04:05,542 --> 00:04:06,417
[door closes]

57
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:09,500
[sighs]

58
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:10,792
[music concludes]

59
00:04:17,875 --> 00:04:19,750
If there's nothing else, I'll get going.

60
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,167
Did you do it?

61
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:24,292
[car door slams]

62
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:25,542
[breathes shakily]

63
00:04:27,042 --> 00:04:28,542
Do you think I did it?

64
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,083
The evidence doesn't look good, you know?

65
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:37,042
Is that your answer?

66
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,875
[Rit] Tell me the truth.

67
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,083
[Mek] The truth?

68
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,458
The truth is Techin was a pain in my ass.

69
00:04:53,542 --> 00:04:55,083
I'd been pissed off for a long time.

70
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:56,708
There was a golf club right there.

71
00:04:56,792 --> 00:04:58,208
So I smashed his head in.

72
00:04:58,292 --> 00:05:00,375
I just kept hitting him until he was dead.

73
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:06,708
Happy now?

74
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:16,792
- I just want to help.
- Help with what?!

75
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,292
Help with what?

76
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:24,542
A man like you…

77
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,500
Since when have you ever put
your family before your work?

78
00:05:28,958 --> 00:05:31,375
Even now, just to come see your son…

79
00:05:31,458 --> 00:05:33,292
Your son who's in jail…

80
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:35,542
You didn't even dare
to bring your own car.

81
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,250
[somber music playing]

82
00:05:40,417 --> 00:05:41,333
[scoffs]

83
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:44,625
Afraid you won't make Chief Judge? Huh?

84
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,292
Afraid having a murderer for a son
will cost you the position?

85
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:50,667
Don't worry. Don't you worry at all.

86
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,958
I won't cause you any more trouble.

87
00:05:53,042 --> 00:05:55,417
But I'll find a way
to pay you back for the bail.

88
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:00,792
- [car door slams]
- [tense music playing]

89
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:05,750
[officer]<i> Based on witness interviews</i>
<i>at the scene of the crime,</i>

90
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:10,000
the presumed motive for the murder
of Mr. Techin Methaneepaisal

91
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:11,958
stems from a romantic dispute.

92
00:06:12,042 --> 00:06:14,417
We found evidence
in the deceased's chat history.

93
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:17,958
The suspect was allegedly jealous
and resentful of his ex-lover,

94
00:06:18,042 --> 00:06:20,417
Ms. Angsumalin Thumnart.

95
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,000
This led him to go
to the deceased's residence

96
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,583
where he committed the crime.

97
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:27,667
<i>The police have refused to comment</i>

98
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,708
<i>on the photos circulating online</i>

99
00:06:29,792 --> 00:06:31,958
<i>of Ms. Angsumalin Thumnart,</i>

100
00:06:32,042 --> 00:06:35,833
<i>the daughter of Dr. Atchara Thumnart,</i>
<i>the leader of the Ruam Thai Party,</i>

101
00:06:35,917 --> 00:06:38,542
<i>who was seen with the suspect, Mr. Mek--</i>

102
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:39,792
[video stops]

103
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:43,917
- [tense music continues]
- [camera shutters clicking]

104
00:06:45,417 --> 00:06:48,208
[reporter 1] Ms. Atchara,
regarding the murder of Chief Anan's son,

105
00:06:48,292 --> 00:06:50,250
the police believe the motive
was a romantic dispute

106
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:52,000
and your daughter has been mentioned.

107
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:53,583
I doubt there's anything to it.

108
00:06:53,667 --> 00:06:55,958
People probably just know
our two families are close.

109
00:06:56,042 --> 00:06:58,000
[reporter 2]
Are you concerned this will be used

110
00:06:58,083 --> 00:06:59,542
to make you a target

111
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:01,917
in the upcoming no-confidence debate?

112
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,708
Wow, that's quite a stretch.

113
00:07:03,792 --> 00:07:05,833
The two aren't related at all.

114
00:07:05,917 --> 00:07:09,500
I think our focus should be on the victim.

115
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:11,000
[reporter 3] Will Ms. Ang be removed

116
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:13,333
from the Fisheries Act committee?

117
00:07:13,417 --> 00:07:15,625
[reporter 4] What is the party's statement
on the matter?

118
00:07:15,708 --> 00:07:17,958
[reporter 2] Will this affect confidence
in the parliament?

119
00:07:18,625 --> 00:07:20,417
[guard 1] You can't come through.

120
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,667
[guard 2] You can't come in.

121
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,250
[music concludes]

122
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,417
[reporter over video]
<i>In an interview just moments ago,</i>

123
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,458
<i>Ruam Thai Party leader,</i>
<i>Ms. Atchara, confirmed</i>

124
00:07:33,542 --> 00:07:34,750
<i>her daughter is not involved…</i>

125
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,458
[Atchara] Take a break, sweetie.

126
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:39,167
The more you watch,
the more stressed you'll get.

127
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:42,000
- [video stops]
- Here, I had Nit get you some vitamins.

128
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,083
[Ang sighs]

129
00:07:44,542 --> 00:07:46,125
That's a pretty lipstick color.

130
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,625
But let's put on a little more.

131
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,208
So you don't look washed out in photos.

132
00:07:54,125 --> 00:07:55,792
I know you don't like this.

133
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,750
But you're in the spotlight now.

134
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:01,375
Where you go, who you're with,

135
00:08:01,458 --> 00:08:04,542
how you dress…
We have to be more careful now.

136
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:07,667
Because people are always looking
for a chance to take us down.

137
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:10,833
Am I making things difficult for you?

138
00:08:10,917 --> 00:08:13,042
Not at all. Don't you worry about me.

139
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:15,083
I've been through a lot.

140
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:17,833
Right now, you just focus
on rebranding the party.

141
00:08:17,917 --> 00:08:21,750
You look ahead. I'll handle the rest.

142
00:08:25,958 --> 00:08:27,292
[door opens]

143
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:31,167
We have to go to Techin's funeral tonight.

144
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:33,125
I've already picked out two outfits.

145
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:34,625
You can choose which one.

146
00:08:34,708 --> 00:08:37,792
[dark intriguing music playing]

147
00:08:44,875 --> 00:08:46,042
[door closes]

148
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:58,292
[breathes deeply]

149
00:09:04,042 --> 00:09:06,292
[dark intriguing music continues]

150
00:09:08,167 --> 00:09:10,875
[overlapping chatter]

151
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:26,292
Father, Lieutenant General Sutthichai
and his wife are here.

152
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:27,625
- Sir.
- [music concludes]

153
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,292
[Sutthichai] My deepest condolences.

154
00:09:34,417 --> 00:09:35,500
[sighs softly]

155
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,500
Thank you for coming.

156
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:40,792
[chatter continues]

157
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:50,208
I'm so sorry for your loss.

158
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,708
It was such a shock.

159
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:56,875
If there's anything we can do to help,
please let us know.

160
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,708
You don't believe those ridiculous
news reports, do you?

161
00:10:03,792 --> 00:10:06,958
The ones saying Ang and that boy
had met in secret before it happened?

162
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:11,167
The photo in the news was from the day
our party gave aid to the community

163
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,292
where the waste processing plant
burned down.

164
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:16,792
Mek was the defendant's lawyer.
We ran into each other by accident.

165
00:10:17,542 --> 00:10:20,208
[soft tense music playing]

166
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:28,667
Ang, you know your mother and I
go way back.

167
00:10:29,542 --> 00:10:31,583
It's hard for a woman in politics.

168
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:35,875
Your mother has survived this long

169
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:39,125
because she chose
to stand on the right side.

170
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:46,458
I hope that particular skill
has been passed down to you.

171
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:52,833
Choose correctly, and you'll go far.

172
00:11:11,458 --> 00:11:13,667
You and Mek aren't
in contact anymore, right?

173
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:19,833
Be careful, Ang.

174
00:11:20,792 --> 00:11:23,917
I don't want Anan to think
you're involved in this.

175
00:11:26,917 --> 00:11:29,542
Anan is not someone you want as an enemy.

176
00:11:32,542 --> 00:11:34,333
I don't believe Mek did it.

177
00:11:34,417 --> 00:11:35,958
[music falls]

178
00:11:36,042 --> 00:11:38,625
What matters more
is what other people believe.

179
00:11:39,792 --> 00:11:42,083
[music rises]

180
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,833
[music concludes]

181
00:11:55,917 --> 00:11:57,208
[Tom]<i> I don't agree.</i>

182
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,667
If we argue that a third party did it,

183
00:12:01,542 --> 00:12:03,542
we have absolutely no evidence
to support it.

184
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:07,375
You don't even know
the Burmese woman's name.

185
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:12,042
So you want me to use
the affair story they just made up?

186
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:17,083
Look, we need to bring up
the victim's history of threats.

187
00:12:18,083 --> 00:12:20,875
We have proof of the money transfers.
We even have the call logs.

188
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:23,667
We'll say he pressured you to go see him,

189
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,000
using your ex as an excuse.

190
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:28,500
When you got there, you argued,
and things got physical.

191
00:12:28,583 --> 00:12:31,125
He attacked you,
so you defended yourself.

192
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,917
But, sir, if we do that,

193
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,875
it's like we're admitting I killed Techin.

194
00:12:35,958 --> 00:12:38,875
We can repeat this a hundred times,
and I'll still say I didn't do it.

195
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:40,042
Right now,

196
00:12:41,542 --> 00:12:43,000
there are only two people

197
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:46,708
who the evidence proves
were at the crime scene.

198
00:12:48,417 --> 00:12:50,042
Techin and you.

199
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:59,000
If you insist on pleading not guilty,

200
00:13:00,458 --> 00:13:01,625
what happens if you lose?

201
00:13:02,958 --> 00:13:08,083
Even if it's manslaughter,
the maximum sentence is 15 years.

202
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:10,625
Is that what you want?

203
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:17,333
[soft tense music playing]

204
00:13:17,417 --> 00:13:20,000
The reason you want me to confess…
is it because of him?

205
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:21,042
[Tom sighs]

206
00:13:21,125 --> 00:13:22,167
[scoffs softly]

207
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:24,708
[sighs]

208
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:27,792
You're too prejudiced against your father.

209
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:30,875
He's worried about you.

210
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:33,458
He's been calling me every single day.

211
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:35,542
You know as well as I do,

212
00:13:36,417 --> 00:13:38,958
how careful he is
about remaining impartial.

213
00:13:40,875 --> 00:13:41,958
[can hisses, cracks]

214
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:51,750
[sighs deeply]

215
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,417
Mek, I've known you since you were born.

216
00:14:00,417 --> 00:14:03,750
Do you really think
I want to see you end up in prison?

217
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,083
But we're coming in empty-handed.

218
00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:07,917
We have nothing to fight them with.

219
00:14:09,792 --> 00:14:11,333
If we fold now…

220
00:14:13,167 --> 00:14:14,667
the damage might be less.

221
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:22,792
I understand.

222
00:14:24,292 --> 00:14:27,375
CRIMINAL COURT

223
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:29,875
[soft tense music continues]

224
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:36,792
Don't worry.

225
00:14:37,292 --> 00:14:38,667
As soon as this is over,

226
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,000
- I'll file for your bail.
- [music concludes]

227
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:46,458
Case number O.927/2568.

228
00:14:46,542 --> 00:14:50,000
The prosecution charges Mr. Mek Piriyawich

229
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:53,625
with the murder
of Mr. Techin Methaneepaisal,

230
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:56,583
accusing him of committing
premeditated murder.

231
00:14:57,292 --> 00:15:00,667
Under Criminal Code Section 289(4),

232
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,750
the offense is punishable by death.

233
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:05,333
- [ominous music playing]
- Why Section 289, Your Honor?

234
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,833
I believe this charge goes
beyond the facts.

235
00:15:09,542 --> 00:15:11,125
The charge stands.

236
00:15:11,208 --> 00:15:14,292
The defendant and the deceased
had a dispute over an affair.

237
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:17,583
Witnesses saw them arguing
outside the courtroom.

238
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:21,792
Furthermore, the defendant traveled to
the victim's home in Saraburi province.

239
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:23,083
That's key evidence.

240
00:15:23,167 --> 00:15:26,167
It indicates the defendant
had malicious intent toward the victim

241
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,583
and suggests the act was premeditated.

242
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:29,625
[scoffs]

243
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:33,250
I believe the indictment is an overreach,
Your Honor.

244
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:36,167
We have records of money transfers
and phone calls

245
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:38,167
which suggest that the deceased

246
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:40,833
pressured the defendant
to come to his home.

247
00:15:40,917 --> 00:15:42,542
As for the weapon at the scene,

248
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:45,042
it was already in the deceased's home.

249
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:49,500
This proves that the defendant
didn't plan this in advance.

250
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:50,583
[music concludes]

251
00:15:50,667 --> 00:15:51,917
The defendant is a lawyer.

252
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,667
He knows the law well.

253
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:59,000
He'd know exactly what to do
to make his case look better.

254
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,292
- That's clearly biased.
- [tense music playing]

255
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:03,458
I can file a complaint.

256
00:16:03,542 --> 00:16:05,083
Watch yourself, Counselor.

257
00:16:06,292 --> 00:16:08,750
Contempt of court is a serious offense.

258
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:13,417
If you wish to file a complaint, go ahead.
You have the right.

259
00:16:14,583 --> 00:16:15,875
But don't threaten me.

260
00:16:18,083 --> 00:16:19,583
[sighs deeply]

261
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:30,833
So, did the defendant commit the crime
as the prosecution alleges?

262
00:16:41,542 --> 00:16:43,542
I plead not guilty to all charges.

263
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:45,917
[suspenseful music playing]

264
00:16:50,083 --> 00:16:51,375
So the defendant will fight this?

265
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:53,042
I will.

266
00:16:58,208 --> 00:16:59,833
What's your defense? Go on.

267
00:17:01,792 --> 00:17:03,667
My defense is that a third party did it.

268
00:17:04,417 --> 00:17:06,917
A foreign woman
who worked for the deceased.

269
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,625
I believe she had been abused
for a long time.

270
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,833
I noticed bruises on her arms.

271
00:17:12,792 --> 00:17:16,833
On the day of the incident,
the deceased shot at her first.

272
00:17:16,917 --> 00:17:20,292
After that, she used a golf club
to beat him to death.

273
00:17:20,375 --> 00:17:21,458
And then she fled.

274
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,875
But everything you've just said

275
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:26,792
has no basis
in the official investigation.

276
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:30,833
Not about the gun, nor this third party.

277
00:17:30,917 --> 00:17:32,917
Can you provide any evidence to prove

278
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,833
that this woman actually exists?

279
00:17:35,917 --> 00:17:37,375
[music concludes]

280
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:38,708
Yes, absolutely.

281
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:44,208
I will find circumstantial evidence
and proof to fight my case.

282
00:17:45,417 --> 00:17:47,042
So you have nothing right now.

283
00:17:47,125 --> 00:17:48,667
[suspenseful music resumes]

284
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,125
Think carefully.

285
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,292
If you confess now,

286
00:17:58,375 --> 00:18:00,667
your sentence will be reduced by half.

287
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:03,167
But if you insist on fighting this,

288
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:06,708
you could end up with the maximum penalty.

289
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:15,708
So, did you commit the crime
you are accused of?

290
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:21,500
May I confer with my client?

291
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:23,583
I stand by my plea of not guilty.

292
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,083
[music intensifies]

293
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:27,833
And I'll request bail to fight the case.

294
00:18:34,292 --> 00:18:36,250
- [music concludes]
- [footsteps approaching]

295
00:18:37,417 --> 00:18:38,667
Any news?

296
00:18:39,542 --> 00:18:40,875
[Tom] The court denied bail.

297
00:18:42,792 --> 00:18:44,833
But we had submitted everything required.

298
00:18:44,917 --> 00:18:46,875
And I don't even have a record, Uncle.

299
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:50,750
They filed an objection to your bail
in advance,

300
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:53,167
claiming you're a flight risk.

301
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,125
I've already filed an appeal.

302
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:57,542
But the court upheld its decision.

303
00:18:57,625 --> 00:18:59,250
This isn't normal, Uncle.

304
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,750
Evidence has disappeared
from the crime scene.

305
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:04,542
I'm sure Anan is trying to frame me.

306
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,958
[Tom] We still have to follow procedure.

307
00:19:09,042 --> 00:19:10,958
How is any of this procedural, Uncle?

308
00:19:11,042 --> 00:19:12,875
Look at what's happening to me.

309
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:18,833
Bail is supposed to be
a right for everyone, isn't it?

310
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:24,958
There's another way.

311
00:19:26,417 --> 00:19:28,000
Use your father's position as collateral.

312
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:36,542
You know I'd never ask him for help.

313
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:38,667
Do you have a better idea, Mek?

314
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:40,667
Hm?

315
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:44,042
If you have a plan, tell me.

316
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:46,542
I'll get it done right now.

317
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:53,000
If not,

318
00:19:53,958 --> 00:19:55,583
then I'm doing this my way.

319
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:57,750
[pensive music playing]

320
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,375
[door opens]

321
00:20:05,292 --> 00:20:06,417
[door closes]

322
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:30,917
[Rit] If that's the only way,
then so be it.

323
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,250
[music concludes]

324
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,333
I think Anan must hold a serious grudge.

325
00:20:39,083 --> 00:20:40,708
Mek picked a fight with the wrong person.

326
00:20:43,042 --> 00:20:45,750
I'm not sure if there's more to it.

327
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,583
Right before this happened,

328
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:54,167
Mek was the defense attorney
in the waste plant fire case

329
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,500
but Anan's son was the co-prosecutor.

330
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:01,000
At first, the defendant confessed.

331
00:21:01,083 --> 00:21:02,958
But later, they recanted their testimony.

332
00:21:03,042 --> 00:21:04,625
Mek was gathering evidence.

333
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:06,917
And who was the judge on that case?

334
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,167
Padung.

335
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:11,000
[ominous musical sting plays]

336
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:13,708
Padung is Anan's man.

337
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:17,042
It could be a coincidence.

338
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:18,750
[soft intriguing music playing]

339
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:21,333
But it's a coincidence
I want to look into.

340
00:21:21,417 --> 00:21:24,542
RIT PIRIYAWICH

341
00:21:24,625 --> 00:21:25,750
[pen clatters]

342
00:21:26,542 --> 00:21:27,500
[sighs]

343
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,125
Revenge for his son is one thing.

344
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:36,167
But if there are other interests involved,

345
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:39,000
frankly, I'm worried about Mek.

346
00:21:42,583 --> 00:21:44,375
I'm leaving him in your hands.

347
00:21:44,458 --> 00:21:46,000
I can't get too involved.

348
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:49,708
As for the bail,
if my signature alone isn't enough,

349
00:21:49,792 --> 00:21:51,500
I might have to talk to them myself.

350
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:55,958
But will that affect your promotion
to Chief Judge?

351
00:21:57,792 --> 00:21:59,042
We'll see.

352
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:03,417
[sighs]

353
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:06,750
[door opens]

354
00:22:08,167 --> 00:22:09,333
[door closes]

355
00:22:10,083 --> 00:22:11,875
- [sighs deeply]
- [music concludes]

356
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:14,458
[Tom] I already spoke to your father.

357
00:22:14,542 --> 00:22:16,167
You just need to sign.

358
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,125
But it's too late to file for bail today.

359
00:22:18,208 --> 00:22:19,667
I'll come by early tomorrow.

360
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:24,417
Don't worry about your safety.

361
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,458
I'll arrange things with my friend
who's a warden.

362
00:22:26,542 --> 00:22:27,792
He'll look after you.

363
00:22:28,583 --> 00:22:31,167
[Jittri] The Director of Prisons
is close to Anan.

364
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:33,875
You think some low-level warden
can actually protect him?

365
00:22:33,958 --> 00:22:35,250
Why are you here?

366
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:36,417
To help bail Mek out.

367
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:40,042
What are you talking about?
I can report you for this.

368
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,000
Go ahead. The sooner, the better.

369
00:22:42,083 --> 00:22:45,250
Then I can report to the Bar Council
and handle the other cases too.

370
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:46,542
- [Tom] Get out.
- Uncle.

371
00:22:48,542 --> 00:22:49,792
I called her here.

372
00:22:49,875 --> 00:22:51,792
[soft tense music playing]

373
00:22:52,625 --> 00:22:55,667
Since you can't help me,
I had to find another option, right?

374
00:22:57,417 --> 00:23:00,542
If you can get me out on bail today,
I'll hire you as my lawyer.

375
00:23:01,167 --> 00:23:02,917
- [in English] Deal.
- [in Thai] Wait, Mek.

376
00:23:03,917 --> 00:23:06,417
- Think carefully.
- What else do I have to lose, Uncle?

377
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:10,000
You said it yourself.
I'm up against a top cop like Anan.

378
00:23:10,083 --> 00:23:12,333
I have to find someone who can save me.

379
00:23:13,042 --> 00:23:14,500
If you choose to hire her,

380
00:23:14,583 --> 00:23:17,708
you're practically
admitting guilt for all charges.

381
00:23:17,792 --> 00:23:19,292
If you're finished, you can leave now.

382
00:23:19,375 --> 00:23:20,792
I need to speak with my client.

383
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:23,000
[music concludes]

384
00:23:23,083 --> 00:23:24,292
Uncle.

385
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:26,875
Thank you for everything.

386
00:23:28,375 --> 00:23:30,917
[soft tense music resumes]

387
00:23:43,917 --> 00:23:45,125
[door closes]

388
00:23:45,208 --> 00:23:47,167
You're going with a third-party defense?

389
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:48,792
[music concludes]

390
00:23:48,875 --> 00:23:50,417
What's your evidence?

391
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:53,208
[unsettling music playing]

392
00:23:58,583 --> 00:24:01,542
[distorted footsteps echoing]

393
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:09,792
[distorted sobbing]

394
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:13,792
[dark intriguing music playing]

395
00:24:18,083 --> 00:24:19,417
- [sobs]
- [heavy thud]

396
00:24:20,083 --> 00:24:21,083
[heavy thud]

397
00:24:21,917 --> 00:24:22,875
[echoing thud]

398
00:24:22,958 --> 00:24:24,250
[Jittri] What's your evidence?

399
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:26,000
The fingerprints on the golf club.

400
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:28,625
Are you sure her fingerprints are on it?

401
00:24:30,458 --> 00:24:31,458
[Mek] I don't think so.

402
00:24:31,542 --> 00:24:33,167
The woman was probably wearing gloves.

403
00:24:34,375 --> 00:24:35,833
And did you touch that club?

404
00:24:37,875 --> 00:24:39,167
[Mek] Yes, I did.

405
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:40,875
There was a moment I grabbed the club.

406
00:24:40,958 --> 00:24:43,208
So the only prints and DNA
on the golf club

407
00:24:43,292 --> 00:24:44,875
will be yours and the victim's.

408
00:24:50,958 --> 00:24:52,125
[Mek] They're on the gun, too.

409
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:55,250
[Jittri] But the police didn't find a gun.

410
00:24:55,333 --> 00:24:57,208
[Mek] I think that woman took it.

411
00:24:57,292 --> 00:24:59,667
[Nay Oo sobbing]

412
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:01,792
But that woman was shot in the leg.

413
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:03,458
There must have been a trail of blood.

414
00:25:05,042 --> 00:25:07,625
Ripping up the grass
and laying new sod is easy.

415
00:25:08,542 --> 00:25:11,792
You think a guy like Anan would leave
a blood trail for you to find?

416
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:16,083
See? For you, it's all a dead end.

417
00:25:16,167 --> 00:25:18,958
You thought if you could find that woman
and the gun, it would be over.

418
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,417
But I don't believe you'll find them.

419
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:22,542
[music concludes]

420
00:25:23,833 --> 00:25:25,542
So if it were you, what would you do?

421
00:25:26,125 --> 00:25:27,750
Let's just say I can handle it.

422
00:25:28,625 --> 00:25:30,333
So, do you want me to start or not?

423
00:25:35,917 --> 00:25:36,792
[object clatters]

424
00:25:36,875 --> 00:25:37,917
[pen clicks]

425
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,833
POWER OF ATTORNEY

426
00:25:39,917 --> 00:25:42,875
[dark daring music playing]

427
00:25:46,542 --> 00:25:48,458
[dark daring music continues]

428
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:50,625
[tires screeching]

429
00:25:58,125 --> 00:26:01,458
[Jittri] <i>You know it's usually hard</i>
<i>to get bail in court.</i>

430
00:26:01,542 --> 00:26:03,792
<i>The key player is Judge Yuthana.</i>

431
00:26:03,875 --> 00:26:05,708
<i>He's the one who approves the request.</i>

432
00:26:05,792 --> 00:26:08,500
<i>We have to do whatever it takes</i>
<i>to get him to sign</i>

433
00:26:08,583 --> 00:26:10,917
<i>before you're sent to prison at six.</i>

434
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,417
[lively chatter]

435
00:26:18,333 --> 00:26:21,083
- [ballon pops]
- [kids cheering]

436
00:26:21,167 --> 00:26:23,000
[dark daring music continues]

437
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:28,375
[Jittri] <i>Today, Yuthana's daughter</i>
<i>is performing at her school festival.</i>

438
00:26:28,458 --> 00:26:30,917
<i>He and his wife will definitely be there.</i>

439
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,875
[pop music playing over speakers]

440
00:26:32,958 --> 00:26:34,708
[phone camera clicking]

441
00:26:44,958 --> 00:26:45,875
[music fades]

442
00:26:45,958 --> 00:26:48,125
Hello, Judge Yuthana.

443
00:26:48,208 --> 00:26:49,958
What a coincidence seeing you here.

444
00:26:50,625 --> 00:26:51,667
Hello, ma'am.

445
00:26:52,208 --> 00:26:54,542
- Hello.
- I'm a lawyer.

446
00:26:54,625 --> 00:26:56,750
So I see Judge Yuthana quite often.

447
00:26:56,833 --> 00:26:59,250
You're even more beautiful in person.

448
00:26:59,333 --> 00:27:01,125
Oh, not at all. [chuckles]

449
00:27:01,625 --> 00:27:04,333
I brought my niece
to check out the festival.

450
00:27:04,417 --> 00:27:06,292
Your niece goes here too? What grade?

451
00:27:06,375 --> 00:27:09,000
Oh, she doesn't.
I just brought her for the festival.

452
00:27:09,625 --> 00:27:11,250
My niece is playing right over there.

453
00:27:14,167 --> 00:27:16,625
She's probably a few years younger
than your daughter.

454
00:27:19,792 --> 00:27:21,917
- [man speaking indistinctly]
- [unsettling music playing]

455
00:27:24,792 --> 00:27:26,500
- [pop music concludes]
- [audience applauding]

456
00:27:26,583 --> 00:27:29,417
[Yuthana] I need to talk
to the ambassador for a moment.

457
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:30,667
[Yuthana's wife] Okay.

458
00:27:37,042 --> 00:27:39,583
What's going on?
Why is our daughter here?

459
00:27:39,667 --> 00:27:42,708
[mistress] <i>What? Didn't you send someone</i>
<i>to pick her up?</i>

460
00:27:43,625 --> 00:27:46,375
<i>A woman with curly hair and a big guy.</i>

461
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,917
<i>The woman said she was your secretary.</i>

462
00:27:51,958 --> 00:27:54,917
[in English] <i>Hello? Hello, Yuth?</i>

463
00:27:56,375 --> 00:27:58,708
- [in Thai] I don't have a secretary.
- [mistress] <i>What?</i>

464
00:27:58,792 --> 00:28:02,625
<i>Who is she then?</i>
<i>She said she's your secretary.</i>

465
00:28:02,708 --> 00:28:04,083
<i>- She said she--</i>
- I have to go.

466
00:28:04,167 --> 00:28:06,417
Our daughter is here. She's safe.

467
00:28:06,500 --> 00:28:08,375
- [mistress] <i>What's going on?</i>
- I'll call you back.

468
00:28:08,458 --> 00:28:10,292
- [mistress] <i>How's our daughter--</i>
- [phone clicks]

469
00:28:12,375 --> 00:28:14,125
What the hell do you think you're doing?

470
00:28:15,042 --> 00:28:16,250
How do you know about this?

471
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,083
About what?

472
00:28:18,708 --> 00:28:21,542
About how you denied a bail request
on someone's orders.

473
00:28:21,625 --> 00:28:24,083
Or about the prostitute
you've been keeping as a mistress?

474
00:28:24,167 --> 00:28:25,417
[Yuthana] Hey, this is insane.

475
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:27,708
How dare you use a child as a pawn?

476
00:28:28,208 --> 00:28:29,667
I'll have you charged with kidnapping.

477
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:31,000
How is it kidnapping?

478
00:28:31,083 --> 00:28:33,125
I was just bringing a little girl
to her dad.

479
00:28:33,208 --> 00:28:35,042
[unsettling music continues]

480
00:28:40,708 --> 00:28:42,500
What do you want? Just say it.

481
00:28:43,542 --> 00:28:46,417
I have a bail request form
that I'd like you to sign.

482
00:28:47,250 --> 00:28:50,500
If it's convenient for you,
I'd like my client released today.

483
00:28:51,542 --> 00:28:53,417
You have no idea who you're messing with.

484
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:56,208
Oh, I do. The question is, do you?

485
00:28:56,792 --> 00:28:59,458
Yiwha, sweetie? Auntie's right here.

486
00:28:59,542 --> 00:29:00,542
Okay!

487
00:29:00,625 --> 00:29:02,875
- [Jittri] I'm coming right over, okay?
- Okay!

488
00:29:07,125 --> 00:29:08,500
[Jittri] Such a sweet voice.

489
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:11,625
Can you hear her? You miss her?

490
00:29:12,792 --> 00:29:14,667
You've crossed a serious line.

491
00:29:14,750 --> 00:29:17,583
Don't worry about me.
Worry about yourself first.

492
00:29:17,667 --> 00:29:19,125
Do you have a lawyer yet?

493
00:29:19,875 --> 00:29:24,125
Divorce cases and asset division
are my specialty, actually.

494
00:29:32,458 --> 00:29:34,542
[music fades]

495
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:36,292
[lock clunking]

496
00:29:36,375 --> 00:29:38,417
[foreboding music playing]

497
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:40,875
[chains jangling]

498
00:29:54,750 --> 00:29:57,875
[chains jangling]

499
00:30:11,292 --> 00:30:13,167
[music concludes]

500
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,458
CENTRAL MALE CORRECTIONAL FACILITY

501
00:30:18,167 --> 00:30:20,458
THE CRIMINAL COURT OPERATES DURING LUNCH

502
00:30:20,542 --> 00:30:23,833
[tense music playing]

503
00:30:25,625 --> 00:30:27,583
I'm here to post bail for Mek Piriyawich.

504
00:30:27,667 --> 00:30:30,292
Case number O.927/2568.

505
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:35,833
If you're posting bail now,
it's cash only.

506
00:30:41,333 --> 00:30:42,333
[Jittri] Two million.

507
00:30:42,958 --> 00:30:44,000
Exactly.

508
00:30:46,125 --> 00:30:48,833
- [engine rumbling]
- [tense music continues]

509
00:30:52,375 --> 00:30:53,583
[prisoner] Hey, pretty boy.

510
00:30:54,458 --> 00:30:55,667
Hey, pretty boy.

511
00:30:57,333 --> 00:30:59,458
You're Techin's friend, right?

512
00:31:01,958 --> 00:31:04,042
He asked us to take special care of you.

513
00:31:04,125 --> 00:31:06,875
[ominous music playing]

514
00:31:14,417 --> 00:31:17,625
[music builds]

515
00:31:17,708 --> 00:31:19,292
- [music falls]
- [clock ticking]

516
00:31:19,375 --> 00:31:20,542
[finger tapping]

517
00:31:22,917 --> 00:31:25,208
[tense music overlapping]

518
00:31:29,750 --> 00:31:31,625
Why aren't you using a money counter?

519
00:31:34,417 --> 00:31:35,875
It's broken.

520
00:31:36,750 --> 00:31:38,417
Do you want me to help you count?

521
00:31:38,500 --> 00:31:39,500
[sighs]

522
00:31:40,042 --> 00:31:41,792
It would be more helpful
if you were quiet.

523
00:31:44,292 --> 00:31:47,500
- [clock ticking]
- [music intensifies]

524
00:31:52,458 --> 00:31:54,250
[music concludes]

525
00:31:57,292 --> 00:31:59,000
[warden 1] Keep going straight!

526
00:31:59,708 --> 00:32:02,417
Come on! More! More!

527
00:32:02,500 --> 00:32:03,500
Stop!

528
00:32:04,125 --> 00:32:05,708
Go, go, go!

529
00:32:05,792 --> 00:32:08,292
[intense music playing]

530
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:10,792
Hurry up!

531
00:32:11,833 --> 00:32:13,750
[warden 2] Go on, get off the bus! Go!

532
00:32:14,625 --> 00:32:16,167
- Let's go. Move it.
- Go!

533
00:32:18,167 --> 00:32:20,083
[warden 2] Hurry up and get inside! Go!

534
00:32:27,375 --> 00:32:28,500
[warden 3] Hey! Do it.

535
00:32:29,292 --> 00:32:31,083
[warden 4] Strip off your clothes!

536
00:32:31,167 --> 00:32:32,833
Pants off too!

537
00:32:32,917 --> 00:32:35,250
[intense music continues]

538
00:32:48,292 --> 00:32:50,167
What the hell are you waiting for?
Strip now!

539
00:32:50,250 --> 00:32:52,000
[music falls]

540
00:33:01,167 --> 00:33:02,333
Strip.

541
00:33:06,333 --> 00:33:08,000
Bastard, I told you to strip!

542
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,083
[pants rustling]

543
00:33:11,167 --> 00:33:13,750
[belt buckle jangling]

544
00:33:14,625 --> 00:33:15,792
[warden 3] Open your mouth.

545
00:33:16,708 --> 00:33:18,250
- Open it.
- [clock ticking]

546
00:33:19,042 --> 00:33:20,167
[warden 3] Hurry up!

547
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:23,500
[chokes]

548
00:33:27,625 --> 00:33:29,417
[retches, coughs]

549
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:30,750
[retches]

550
00:33:31,333 --> 00:33:32,625
[warden 3] You stubborn bastard!

551
00:33:32,708 --> 00:33:34,125
Get on the floor!

552
00:33:35,792 --> 00:33:38,208
Plenty of friends waiting for you inside.

553
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,042
[music intensifies]

554
00:33:44,083 --> 00:33:45,625
[breathes shakily]

555
00:33:45,708 --> 00:33:46,750
[warden 4] Mek, right?

556
00:33:47,917 --> 00:33:49,167
Mek, right?

557
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:50,667
[clock ticking]

558
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:52,625
- [warden 4] Mek, right?
- [sobs softly]

559
00:33:52,708 --> 00:33:53,875
[warden 4] Get up!

560
00:33:53,958 --> 00:33:55,375
[breathes shakily]

561
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,000
You made bail.

562
00:33:57,083 --> 00:33:59,708
[clock ticking]

563
00:34:05,667 --> 00:34:07,417
- [door opens]
- [clock ticking fades]

564
00:34:08,667 --> 00:34:10,083
[door clangs shut]

565
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:17,792
[dark daring music playing]

566
00:34:38,292 --> 00:34:39,417
[door clangs shut]

567
00:34:40,333 --> 00:34:43,083
[music concludes]

568
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:47,667
Are you thinking about going back in?

569
00:34:56,125 --> 00:34:58,792
- I almost gave up hope back there.
- [Jittri] It's my job.

570
00:34:59,417 --> 00:35:00,500
Get in the car.

571
00:35:04,042 --> 00:35:05,083
[car door opens]

572
00:35:09,708 --> 00:35:10,875
[car door closes]

573
00:35:14,667 --> 00:35:15,792
[seat belt clicks]

574
00:35:16,708 --> 00:35:18,333
We haven't discussed your legal fees.

575
00:35:21,417 --> 00:35:22,875
I'm not taking money for this case.

576
00:35:22,958 --> 00:35:24,458
But you'll have to work for me.

577
00:35:28,292 --> 00:35:29,542
What for?

578
00:35:31,542 --> 00:35:33,917
If you want to beat this case,
you'll do as I say.

579
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:35,917
Or if you think
you can find another lawyer

580
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,792
who'll defend the man accused
of killing Anan's son,

581
00:35:39,875 --> 00:35:40,917
be my guest.

582
00:35:49,792 --> 00:35:52,375
[dark daring music playing]

583
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:54,625
[engine starts]

584
00:36:03,792 --> 00:36:06,583
[music turns suspenseful]

585
00:36:06,667 --> 00:36:08,833
[rain pattering]

586
00:36:20,417 --> 00:36:22,542
The Chief Jailer reported in.
It's Judge Rit's son.

587
00:36:22,625 --> 00:36:23,792
He's been bailed out.

588
00:36:24,875 --> 00:36:27,167
Apparently, he hired a new lawyer
named Jittri.

589
00:36:28,792 --> 00:36:30,292
Is there anything you'd like me to do?

590
00:36:30,375 --> 00:36:32,958
[dark intriguing music playing]

591
00:36:33,042 --> 00:36:35,958
I want to know a little bit more
about this lawyer, Jittri.

592
00:36:40,083 --> 00:36:41,875
[music rises]

593
00:36:41,958 --> 00:36:44,667
[dark intriguing music continues,
intensifies]

594
00:37:50,583 --> 00:37:54,083
[dark tense music playing]

595
00:39:02,875 --> 00:39:04,333
[music concludes]
